
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 08 of Thoracic CT
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Mass clavicle' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' box

When I am on 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Septa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Nidus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Punctiform hyperintensities/thickened vertical trabeculae ("polka dotted sign")' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fatty' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cystic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ground glass aspect' checkbox is enabled
And 'Liquid level' checkbox is enabled

And 'Expansion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteolytic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteoblastic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Permeative growth' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerotic border' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pedunculated, growing from the epiphysis towards the diaphysis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration of adjacent soft tissue' checkbox is enabled

And 'Missing' radio button is enabled
And 'Continuously' radio button is enabled
And 'Interrupted' radio button is enabled

And 'Adjacent sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteoproliferative reaction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pathological fracture' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Calcification' checkbox
Then 'Laminar' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Dystrophic' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Sclerotic border' checkbox
Then 'Geographic' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Continuously' radio button
Then 'Remodelling' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lamination' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Interrupted' radio button
Then 'Spiculated' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sunburst' checkbox is enabled
And 'Codman Triangle' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Adjacent sclerosis' checkbox
Then 'Narrow' radio button is enabled
And 'Broad' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Osteoproliferative reaction' checkbox
Then 'Bone apposition' checkbox is enabled
